English translation of Hempel 1923). 
<emphasis box="[862,1131,1827,1851]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[862,1123,1827,1851]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">Puparium habitus</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Puparium broadly oval, 1570 Î¼m long by 1000 wide, pale with central area darker and abdominal segments distinct. True margin minutely crenulate with two rows of much larger crenulations. Vasiform orifice is large,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[192,1440,195,283]" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">subpyriform, being widest across the anterior part. Operculum small, transversely rectangular, with lateral margins rounded, and does not reach to half the length of the orifice. Lingula is large, thick and spatulate hardly reaching the posterior margin of the of the vasiform orifice.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
